an five of them. Subsequently, the PM+ (uWUE+) model reasonably reproduced eight-day ET over four sites under a dry climate (Arid Index ≤ 0.5) with site-level R2 = 0.691 (0.617) and RMSE = 6.663 (7.906) mm/8d on average, which is better than the six existing models. In addition, the regional mean annual ET varied from 590 mm per year (mm/yr) to 680 mm/yr over NCP with a significant increasing trend of 9.05 mm/yr (p < 0.01), and the ET values in maize growing season were higher than that in wheat growing season. Our results demonstrated that the simply formulated PM+ and uWUE+ models can provide simple and robust approaches to estimate regional and global cropland ET. © 2021 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
