AB  - By undertaking the organization of the 2004 Olympic Games, Greece is facing one of the most important challenges of its recent history. On behalf of the international community, it is being called upon to manage the largest athletic event in the world with flawless organization and contemporary infrastructure and in a secure environment. Our aims in the planning of security for the Olympics are 1. to make the period of the games a time of peace and safety in our country, 2. to ensure that all those involved are able to carry out their duties without hindrance, 3. to give all visitors the essential feeling of security, enabling them to enjoy the Athens Olympics and Greek hospitality in general, and 4. to project to the entire world the image of an event infused with the values of peace, friendship, athletic grace, and competition.
